text.tspan: Is the probability of believing that concealing errors is unethical different
There is very strong evidence that male and female managers have
different probabilities of believing error concealment is unethical.
There is much research interest in ethical decision-making by managers. To
examine differences between males and females, 50 male and 50 female managers
were asked whether concealing one's on-the-job errors was very unethical.
